---
layout: base.njk
title: Cocovox
description: An AI-powered learning platform with adaptive tutoring, literacy-first lessons, and AAC communication tools. Built for every learner.
---

<section class="hero">
  <h1 class="hero__title" style="view-transition-name: page-title;">Cocovox</h1>
  <p class="hero__tagline">AI tutoring that meets every learner where they are.</p>
  <p class="hero__intro">
    2 in 3 American students can't read at grade level. 54 million adults read below sixth grade.
    Cocovox is an AI learning platform built from the ground up to change that — with literacy-first lessons,
    adaptive tutoring, and accessibility as the default.
  </p>
  <div class="hero__actions">
    <a href="https://cocovox.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn--primary btn--large">Visit Cocovox.ai</a>
    <a href="https://youtube.com/watch?v=placeholder" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn--secondary btn--large">Watch Preview</a>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Core Features -->
<section class="section" aria-label="Features">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="section-heading">What Makes Cocovox Different</h2>

    <div class="carousel" role="list">

      <article class="card" role="listitem">
        <span class="card__eyebrow">Adaptive</span>
        <h3 class="card__title">AI That Learns You</h3>
        <p class="card__description">
          Just chat. Ask for a lesson, a quiz, flashcards, a deep dive — it generates them on the spot.
          Everything adjusts to your level, from 3rd grade to grad school. Create a learning persona that
          fits your style — tweak it, save it, reuse it.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card" role="listitem">
        <span class="card__eyebrow">Literacy First</span>
        <h3 class="card__title">7 Lesson Types, One Practice System</h3>
        <p class="card__description">
          Letter recognition, phoneme blending, sight words, sentence reading — every card has a practice bar.
          Read aloud and get instant word-by-word feedback. Rate how it felt: "Too Easy!" or "Tricky?"
          Spaced repetition schedules your next review automatically.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card" role="listitem">
        <span class="card__eyebrow">Phonemic Awareness</span>
        <h3 class="card__title">The #1 Predictor of Reading Success</h3>
        <p class="card__description">
          Blending ("/c/..../a/..../t/" → "cat"), segmenting, and rhyme matching built into the core —
          not as premium add-ons. Because the science of reading shouldn't be locked behind a paywall.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card" role="listitem">
        <span class="card__eyebrow">Dashboards</span>
        <h3 class="card__title">Progress Parents Actually See</h3>
        <p class="card__description">
          Dashboards update after every session. Weekly emails showing what clicked and what didn't.
          No more "how was tutoring?" followed by a shrug.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card" role="listitem">
        <span class="card__eyebrow">Visual Learning</span>
        <h3 class="card__title">Math & Science Animations</h3>
        <p class="card__description">
          Narrated animations that bring concepts to life. See the math, hear the explanation,
          understand the why — not just the what.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card" role="listitem">
        <span class="card__eyebrow">Accessible</span>
        <h3 class="card__title">Accessibility Is the Default</h3>
        <p class="card__description">
          Every plan includes every feature. No pro tier for accessibility.
          Built for every learner from day one — because it's not a feature, it's the architecture.
        </p>
      </article>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- AAC Spotlight -->
<section class="section" aria-label="AAC Communication" style="background: var(--color-surface-warm);">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="callout callout--scoop" style="max-width: var(--max-width-wide); margin-inline: auto;">
      <h2 class="section-heading">AAC: A Voice for Everyone</h2>
      <p style="font-size: var(--text-lg); color: var(--color-ink-light); max-width: var(--max-width-prose); margin-block-end: var(--space-10); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);">
        Some kids and adults can't speak. If they're fortunate, they have an app that speaks for them.
        Most of those apps show a giant grid of words. It's overwhelming. The voices are robotic.
        The options aren't personalized. We're doing it differently.
      </p>

      <div class="grid grid--3 stagger">

        <div class="feature">
          <span class="feature__icon" aria-hidden="true">🎯</span>
          <h3 class="feature__title">Zone 1: Essential Words</h3>
          <p class="feature__text">
            Eight words that never move. Yes, no, help, more. Always in the same spot.
            Muscle memory matters — if "help" is always in the same place, you can find it without looking.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="feature">
          <span class="feature__icon" aria-hidden="true">⭐</span>
          <h3 class="feature__title">Zone 2: Personal Vocabulary</h3>
          <p class="feature__text">
            Words you use a lot. Star your favorites and they rise to the top.
            Your communication tool should know you.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="feature">
          <span class="feature__icon" aria-hidden="true">🧠</span>
          <h3 class="feature__title">Zone 3: AI Predictions</h3>
          <p class="feature__text">
            AI suggests what you might say next based on context. Connected to your calendar —
            during math class it shows math words. After school: snack, tired, can we play outside.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>

      <div class="grid grid--2 stagger" style="margin-block-start: var(--space-10);">

        <div class="feature">
          <span class="feature__icon" aria-hidden="true">🗣️</span>
          <h3 class="feature__title">100+ AI Voices</h3>
          <p class="feature__text">
            No more robotic voice from 2005. Over 100 options that actually sound human.
            Save presets — a classroom voice for presentations, a friends voice for lunch.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="feature">
          <span class="feature__icon" aria-hidden="true">💰</span>
          <h3 class="feature__title">$19.99/month. No Upsells.</h3>
          <p class="feature__text">
            Most competitors charge $269 upfront with no trial. We offer a free trial,
            then $19.99/month with every feature included. Accessibility is never an add-on.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

